                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/70.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Embassy at this capital is in receipt of a telegram from Richard
                    Keays, a British subject in the district of Juarez, stating that his property is
                    in grave danger from Constitutionalists. Please confer with appropriate
                    authorities and urge upon them the importance of giving suitable protection to
                    the property of Mr. Keays as well as the property of other foreigners in that
                    district.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
